{"questionId":"13963","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Let&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( x \\right) = \\frac{{16}}{x}\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>16</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>. The line <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"L\">\n  <mi>L</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;is tangent to the graph of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n</math></span> at&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = 8\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>8</mn>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"L\">\n  <mi>L</mi>\n</math></span> can be expressed in the form <em><strong>r</strong></em>&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = \\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  8 \\\\   2  \\end{array}} \\right) + t\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>8</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span><em><strong>u</strong></em>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The direction vector of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = x\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> is&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  1 \\\\   1  \\end{array}} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the acute angle between <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = x\"> <mi>y</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mi>x</mi> </math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"L\"> <mi>L</mi> </math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>correct scalar product and magnitudes&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)(A1)(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>scalar product&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = 1 \\times 4 + 1 \\times&nbsp; - 1\\,\\,\\,\\left( { = 3} \\right)\"> <mo>=</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mo>×</mo> <mn>4</mn> <mo>+</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mo>×</mo> <mo>−</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>3</mn> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </math></span></p>\n<p>magnitudes&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = \\sqrt {{1^2} + {1^2}} \"> <mo>=</mo> <msqrt> <mrow> <msup> <mn>1</mn> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <mrow> <msup> <mn>1</mn> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> </msqrt> </math></span>,&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\sqrt {{4^2} + {{\\left( { - 1} \\right)}^2}} \"> <msqrt> <mrow> <msup> <mn>4</mn> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <mrow> <msup> <mrow> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mo>−</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mn>2</mn> </msu